# Content Structure and Organization

This project uses a combination of static HTML content and dynamic JSON-powered sections to create a maintainable and easily updatable academic website.

## JSON Data Files

The project uses three main JSON files in the [data](mdc:data) directory:

- [profile-info.json](mdc:data/profile-info.json): Contains personal information, name, subtitle, and social media links
- [publications.json](mdc:data/publications.json): Stores all publications with metadata for filtering
- [news.json](mdc:data/news.json): Contains news and updates in chronological order

## How Content Is Loaded

The [script.js](mdc:script.js) file contains functions that load data from these JSON files:

1. `loadProfileInfo()`: Loads profile information from profile-info.json
2. `loadPublications()`: Loads and renders publications from publications.json 
3. `renderNewsItems()`: Renders news items from news.json

## Page Structure

- The homepage [index.html](mdc:index.html) contains all main sections.
- Additional pages in the [pages](mdc:pages) directory include:
  - [all-news.html](mdc:pages/all-news.html): Displays the complete list of news items

## Assets Organization

The [assets](mdc:assets) directory contains:
- Profile photos
- University logos
- Social media icons
- Additional images
